  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 10 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 1 critical, 5 high, 15 medium, 18 normal. Key bases needing attention include Larnaca (LCA/LCLK), M. R. Štefánik (BTS/LZIB) and Vienna (VIE/LOWW); plus 3 other bases. 15 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is thunderstorm / convective risk and cold‑temperature performance penalties  — most notably around David the Builder Kutaisi (KUT/UGKO), Larnaca (LCA/LCLK) and Zvartnots (EVN/UDYZ). Network hotspots: Trondheim Airport, Værnes (TRD/ENVA), Tenerife Sur (TFS/GCTS), Brussels South Charleroi (CRL/EBCI), Frankfurt-Hahn (HHN/EDFH), Stockholm Skavsta (NYO/ESKN) and 5 others. Primary drivers: low cloud base, snow / blowing snow and thunderstorm / convective risk. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Trondheim Airport, Værnes (TRD/ENVA), Frankfurt-Hahn (HHN/EDFH), Stockholm Skavsta (NYO/ESKN) and 9 others.",
